0. git clone

1. Use virtualenv to create a Python virtual environment to which you
   can install Python packages.

   python virtualenv-x.y.z/virtualenv.py --no-site-packages --distribute site-root

2. Activate the virtualenv

   cd site-root
   source ./bin/activate

3. Install required packages.

   pip install -r requires.txt

(At this point, a local development server should work.  `python developerInstance.py`)

4. Edit config.yml with local settings.  You must at least set
   application.interpreter to the interpreter in your virtualenv.
